        <section id="configuration">
          <div class="page-header">
            <h1>2. Configuration</h1>
          </div>
          <p class="lead">After you installed BootstrapBundle using Composer you have to add some lines to your apps <code>config.yml</code> and start using it right away</p>

          <div class="row-fluid">
            <div class="span12">
              <h2>Form theme</h2>
              <p>BootstrapBundle can automatically style every form in your application with Twitter Bootstrap. You just need to tell Twig to use the theme that comes with the bundle.</p>
<pre class="prettyprint linenums">
# app/config.yml
twig:
    form:
        resources:
            - "BraincraftedBootstrapBundle:Form:form_div_layout.html.twig"
</pre>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="row-fluid">
            <div class="span12">
              <h2>KnpMenu theme</h2>
              <p>If you want to use KnpMenu to display menus in the Twitter Bootstrap style you have to tell KnpMenu to use the theme provided by BootstrapBundle.</p>
<pre class="prettyprint linenums">
# app/config.yml
knp_menu:
   twig:
       template: "BraincraftedBootstrapBundle:Menu:menu.html.twig"
</pre>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="row-fluid">
            <div class="span12">
              <h2>KnpPaginator theme</h2>
              <p>If you want to use KnpPaginator to display pagination in the Twitter Bootstrap style you have to tell KnpPaginator to use the theme provided by BootstrapBundle.</p>
<pre class="prettyprint linenums">
# app/config.yml
knp_paginator:
    template:
        pagination: BraincraftedBootstrapBundle:Pagination:pagination.html.twig
</pre>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="row-fluid">
            <div class="span12">
              <h2>Use Assetic for Asset Management</h2>
              <p>If you want to manage your assets with Assetic you need add the Twitter Bootstrap CSS or LESS and JavaScript files to your configuration. You can either include the precompiled CSS and JavaScript files in your configuration or you can compile and concatinate the module files using, for example, the following configuration. Of course you can modify the configuration depending on your needs:</p>
<pre class="prettyprint linenums">
# app/config.yml
assetic:
    debug:          %kernel.debug%
    use_controller: false
    bundles:        [ ]
    filters:
        less:
            node:       /usr/local/bin/node
            node_paths: [/usr/local/lib/node_modules]
            apply_to:   "\.less$"
        cssrewrite: ~
    assets:
        bootstrap_css:
            inputs:
                - %kernel.root_dir%/../web/bundles/braincraftedbootstrap/less/bootstrap.less
                - %kernel.root_dir%/../web/bundles/braincraftedbootstrap/less/responsive.less
            filters:
                - less
                - cssrewrite
            output: bundles/braincraftedbootstrap/css/bootstrap.compiled.css
        bootstrap_js:
            inputs:
                - %kernel.root_dir%/../web/bundles/braincraftedbootstrap/js/bootstrap-transition.js
                - %kernel.root_dir%/../web/bundles/braincraftedbootstrap/js/bootstrap-alert.js
                - %kernel.root_dir%/../web/bundles/braincraftedbootstrap/js/bootstrap-button.js
                - %kernel.root_dir%/../web/bundles/braincraftedbootstrap/js/bootstrap-carousel.js
                - %kernel.root_dir%/../web/bundles/braincraftedbootstrap/js/bootstrap-collapse.js
                - %kernel.root_dir%/../web/bundles/braincraftedbootstrap/js/bootstrap-dropdown.js
                - %kernel.root_dir%/../web/bundles/braincraftedbootstrap/js/bootstrap-modal.js
                - %kernel.root_dir%/../web/bundles/braincraftedbootstrap/js/bootstrap-tooltip.js
                - %kernel.root_dir%/../web/bundles/braincraftedbootstrap/js/bootstrap-popover.js
                - %kernel.root_dir%/../web/bundles/braincraftedbootstrap/js/bootstrap-scrollspy.js
                - %kernel.root_dir%/../web/bundles/braincraftedbootstrap/js/bootstrap-tab.js
                - %kernel.root_dir%/../web/bundles/braincraftedbootstrap/js/bootstrap-typeahead.js
                - %kernel.root_dir%/../web/bundles/braincraftedbootstrap/js/bootstrap-affix.js
            output: bundles/braincraftedbootstrap/js/bootstrap.compiled.js
</pre>
            <p>You should also configure you assets in the `config.yml` instead of your template. Learn more about <a href="http://sonata-project.org/blog/2012/5/15/assetic-package-configuration">configuring Assetic</a>.</p>
            <p>You now need to install the assets and dump the assets (the order is important):</p>
<pre class="prettyprint linenums">
$ php app/console assets:install --symlink
$ php app/console assetic:dump
</pre>
            <p>If you change the `output` directory you probably have to manually copy the icons to your `web` directory.</p>
            <p>When you don't want to use Assetic you can include the assets directly. A template is provided in the section <a href="#html-template">HTML template</a>.
            </div>
          </div>
